---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import SectionDivider from "../components/ui/SectionDivider.astro";
import SelfieCarousel from "../components/home/SelfieCarousel.astro";

const title = "Lester Cheong";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} currentPage="profile">
  <header class="header-grid">
    <div class="header-info">
      <h1>Lester Cheong</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">Full-Stack Engineer &amp; Builder · Singapore</p>
    </div>
    <div class="header-selfie">
      <SelfieCarousel />
    </div>
  </header>

  <SectionDivider />

  <section>
    <h2>Summary</h2>
    <p>
      Engineer who ships production systems end-to-end — from database schema to
      deployed frontend. 4+ shipped products across AI, fintech, and commerce.
      Built and operate software serving real paying clients today, not side
      projects.
    </p>
    <p>
      I build AI-native products for SMBs that can't afford engineering teams.
      Three production Telegram bots. One computer-vision photobooth. Multiple
      client-facing web apps. Every system I've built is in production, handling
      real users, real money, real data.
    </p>
    <p>
      Thesis: the cost of software just collapsed. A single engineer with AI
      tooling now delivers what took a team of five. The bottleneck isn't speed
      — it's taste. Knowing what to build, what corners not to cut, and when
      "good enough" ships value faster than "perfect."
    </p>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <section>
    <h2>Experience</h2>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Sales Executive &amp; Technical Consultant</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">JustifyPrint · May 2025 – Present</p>
      <p>
        Wore every hat — sales, engineering, marketing — for a brick-and-mortar
        print shop. Built an AI chatbot that handles customer inquiries and
        captures leads 24/7, turning off-hours traffic into orders. The bot uses
        tool-calling agents (Mastra AI) to walk customers through product
        selection, pricing, and checkout — entirely within Telegram.
      </p>
      <p>
        Rebuilt the company website with analytics. Drove digital transformation
        strategy for a traditional business with zero prior tech infrastructure.
        This is what "AI for SMBs" looks like in practice.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Freelance Software Engineer</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">Self-employed · Dec 2024 – Present</p>
      <p>
        Freelance engineer digitizing operations for SMBs. 3 paying clients.
        Every engagement starts the same way: walk into the business, map their
        workflow on paper, ship a working system within weeks.
      </p>
      <p>
        Flagship product: a Telegram-based order management system for a
        distribution company — 24–26 active daily users, dual-sync to PostgreSQL
        + Google Sheets, role-based access, CRON-scheduled reports. Zero
        downtime since launch. Stack: TypeScript, grammY, Prisma, PostgreSQL.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>API Developer, Digital Channels &amp; OpenBanking</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">OCBC Bank · Apr 2023 – Sep 2024</p>
      <p>
        Enterprise API development at Singapore's second-largest bank (S$13B
        revenue). Owned partner onboarding pipeline for OpenBanking APIs.
        Mentored a cohort of Ignite apprentices building an internal partner
        portal (React + Spring). Managed change tickets across production
        banking systems with zero-downtime deployment requirements.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>IGNITE Apprenticeship, OpenBanking &amp; Partnerships</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">OCBC Bank · Mar 2022 – Mar 2023</p>
      <p>
        Built internal developer tooling from scratch — a Node.js CLI that
        parses Postman collections, auto-generates API assertion tests, and
        renders results on a live dashboard. Reduced manual QA effort for the
        team's API regression suite. Won Rookie of the Year. Volunteered
        teaching JavaScript to secondary school students through Code@OCBC.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>IoT Lock Technician</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">SG Bike · Nov 2018 – Aug 2020</p>
      <p>
        Hardware + software hybrid role at a shared mobility startup. Trained 3
        interns, wrote the team's first troubleshooting docs. Reverse-engineered
        a competitor's lock firmware (acquired via M&A, no keys provided) to
        integrate it into fleet operations — the kind of scrappy problem-solving
        that startups need.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Hackathons</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">
        SuperAI · Jun 2025 &nbsp;|&nbsp; AngelHack · May 2024
      </p>
      <p>
        SuperAI Next Hackathon 2025 — shipped a full-stack TypeScript submission
        in 24 hours. AngelHack 2024 — top 15% finish, placed 29th of 200 teams
        (Seraphim Sentinels).
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <section>
    <h2>Community &amp; Open Source</h2>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>DevsGoWhere</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">
        Singapore Developer Community · Active Contributor
      </p>
      <p>
        Core contributor to Singapore's developer event aggregation platform —
        the go-to resource for local tech meetups and conferences. Embedded in
        the SG dev ecosystem.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Open-Source &amp; AI Tooling</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">GitHub · Ongoing</p>
      <p>
        Shipping MCP servers (Model Context Protocol) that plug into AI coding
        assistants — part of the emerging toolchain that's redefining how
        software gets built. TypeScript project templates, developer utilities,
        and public experiments in AI-assisted development. This portfolio site
        is one of them.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <section>
    <h2>Projects</h2>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>JustifyPrint — AI Sales Agent</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">Justifyprint · 2025 – Present · Production</p>
      <p>
        An AI agent that sells printing services through Telegram. Not a chatbot
        with canned replies — a tool-calling LLM agent that queries live product
        catalogs, calculates pricing with paper/size multipliers, saves order
        drafts, and processes confirmations. Runs 24/7 with conversation memory
        and token-aware context management. One-person build, zero-to-production
        in weeks.
      </p>
      <ul class="project-tags">
        <li>TypeScript</li>
        <li>Mastra AI</li>
        <li>grammY</li>
        <li>Prisma</li>
        <li>Fastify</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL</li>
        <li>Railway</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Tekong Seafood Restaurant — Digital Storefront</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">
        tekong-seafood-restaurant · 2024 – Present · Production
      </p>
      <p>
        PWA for a 35-year heritage restaurant in Singapore. Digitized their
        entire menu from spreadsheets into a searchable, mobile-first
        experience. Embedded media (YouTube celebrity feature, TikTok viral
        clip), seasonal promotional banners, Supabase-backed customer data, and
        offline-first service worker. Helped a traditional F&B business reach
        customers who expect a modern digital presence.
      </p>
      <ul class="project-tags">
        <li>React 18</li>
        <li>TypeScript</li>
        <li>PrimeReact</li>
        <li>Tailwind CSS</li>
        <li>Supabase</li>
        <li>PWA</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Sales Consolidator — Order Pipeline</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">
        uncle-james-giam · 2025 – Present · Production (24–26 daily users)
      </p>
      <p>
        Replaced a manual WhatsApp + spreadsheet workflow with a structured
        order pipeline. Salespersons submit orders via Telegram; data
        dual-writes to PostgreSQL (source of truth) and Google Sheets (for
        non-technical verifiers). Role-based admin flows, CRON-triggered daily
        summaries, custom ESLint rules enforcing bot command consistency. Zero
        data loss since launch. Built for a real distribution company moving
        real inventory.
      </p>
      <ul class="project-tags">
        <li>TypeScript</li>
        <li>grammY</li>
        <li>Fastify</li>
        <li>Google Sheets API</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL</li>
        <li>LangChain</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Events AI Photobooth — Generative Portraits</h3>
      <p class="text-muted">
        client-kendrick · 2026 – Present · Deployed at live events
      </p>
      <p>
        A kiosk that turns a webcam selfie into an AI-styled portrait in
        seconds. Three-service architecture: Vue 3 touch-screen frontend →
        Fastify session API with PostgreSQL → Python FastAPI service running
        IP-Adapter-FaceID-PlusV2 on CUDA (InsightFace face embedding + Stable
        Diffusion 1.5 generation). Users select gender and hairstyle; the
        pipeline generates a photorealistic stylized portrait. Designed for
        high-throughput event environments. Dockerized for portable deployment
        to any venue with a GPU.
      </p>
      <ul class="project-tags">
        <li>Vue 3</li>
        <li>TypeScript</li>
        <li>Python</li>
        <li>FastAPI</li>
        <li>Stable Diffusion</li>
        <li>InsightFace</li>
        <li>Fastify</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL</li>
        <li>Docker</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <section>
    <h2>Technical Competencies</h2>
    {
      (() => {
        const skills = {
          "Languages & Frameworks": [
            { name: "TypeScript", level: 5 },
            { name: "JavaScript", level: 5 },
            { name: "React", level: 5 },
            { name: "Vue", level: 3 },
            { name: "Python", level: 3 },
            { name: "C#", level: 3 },
            { name: "Java", level: 2 },
            { name: "Kotlin", level: 2 },
            { name: "Swift", level: 2 },
            { name: "C++", level: 2 },
          ],
          "Backend & Infrastructure": [
            { name: "Fastify", level: 5 },
            { name: "Prisma", level: 5 },
            { name: "PostgreSQL", level: 5 },
            { name: "Telegram Bot API", level: 5 },
            { name: "Docker", level: 3 },
            { name: "CI/CD", level: 3 },
          ],
          "Frontend & Tooling": [
            { name: "Astro", level: 3 },
            { name: "Vite", level: 3 },
            { name: "Bun", level: 3 },
            { name: "TanStack Query", level: 3 },
          ],
          "AI & Emerging": [
            { name: "MCP Servers", level: 3 },
            { name: "Mastra AI", level: 3 },
            { name: "Stable Diffusion", level: 2 },
            { name: "RAG Applications", level: 2 },
            { name: "LangChain", level: 2 },
            { name: "NLP/ML", level: 2 },
          ],
        };

        const levelClass = (l: number) =>
          l === 5 ? "proficient" : l === 3 ? "working" : "foundational";

        return Object.entries(skills).map(([category, items]) => (
          <div class="skill-category">
            <h3>{category}</h3>
            <ul class="skill-list">
              {items.map(({ name, level }) => (
                <li class={`skill-row ${levelClass(level)}`}>
                  <span class="skill-name">{name}</span>
                  <span class="skill-bars">
                    {[1, 2, 3, 4, 5].map((i) => (
                      <span class={`bar ${i > level ? "dim" : ""}`} />
                    ))}
                  </span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ));
      })()
    }
  </section>

  <SectionDivider />

  <section>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/cheonglol">GitHub</a></li>
      <li>
        <a href="https://sg.linkedin.com/in/lester-cheong-a29a4a209">LinkedIn</a
        >
      </li>
      <li><a href="mailto:lestercheong70@outlook.com">Email</a></li>
      <li><a href="/cheonglol/blog">Blog →</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  @use "../styles/variables" as *;

  .header-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column-reverse;
    gap: $space-3;
    margin-bottom: $space-4;

    @media (min-width: 640px) {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: $space-4;
      align-items: end;
    }
  }

  .header-info {
    h1 {
      margin-bottom: $space-1;
    }
  }

  .header-selfie {
    width: 65%;

    @media (min-width: 640px) {
      width: 100%;
      justify-self: end;
    }
  }

  .card {
    margin-bottom: $space-3;

    h3 {
      margin-bottom: $space-1;
    }

    p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
  }

  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: $space-1;
    margin-bottom: $space-3;
  }

  .skill-legend {
    display: flex;
    gap: $space-4;
    font-size: $font-size-xs;
    color: $text-muted;
    margin-top: $space-2;

    .legend-bar {
      display: inline-block;
      width: 24px;
      height: 4px;
      border-radius: $radius-full;
      margin-right: $space-1;
      vertical-align: middle;

      &.proficient {
        background: $accent;
      }
      &.working {
        background: $purple-400;
      }
      &.foundational {
        background: $grey-500;
      }
    }
  }

  .project-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: $space-1;
    padding-left: 0;
    margin-top: $space-2;

    li {
      list-style: none;
      font-size: $font-size-xs;
      padding: 2px 10px;
      border-radius: $radius-full;
      background: rgba($accent, 0.12);
      color: $accent;
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
  }

  section ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;

    li {
      margin-bottom: $space-1;
    }
  }
</style>
